# Obsidian Doc Sync Rule

When making code changes, update project documentation in the same task.

## Required doc checks after code edits

1. Update these files when relevant:
- `notes/_index.md` (new key docs/entry points)
- `notes/*_architecture.md` (structure, components, data flow changes)
- `notes/*_requirements.md` (behavior/constraints/UX requirements changes)
- `notes/*_release-plan.md` (rollout steps, verification focus, next actions)
- `DECISIONS.md` (non-trivial technical/product decisions)
- `TROUBLESHOOTING.md` (new failure mode + fix/prevention)
- `CHANGELOG_DEV.md` (date entry for what/why/files/related)

2. Keep source of truth clear:
- Do not duplicate full specs into notes.
- In notes, keep concise summaries and add `Source: [[...]]` links to primary docs.

3. Update policy:
- If code behavior changed, update at least one `notes/*` file and `CHANGELOG_DEV.md`.
- If architecture/trade-off changed, append an ADR-style item in `DECISIONS.md`.
- If bug fix was non-obvious, add a short case in `TROUBLESHOOTING.md`.

## Output expectation for each task

Before finishing, report:
- Which docs were updated
- Why those updates were needed
